  "body": "`default-tab-width` is standardly 8, but most programmers and style guides prefer an indentation width smaller than that.  Rust itself uses 4 space indents.  Most other Emacs modes define the indentation width as 4 or 2 spaces, independently of the width of a Tab character.  Depending on `default-tab-width` makes especially little sense for rust-mode because it sets `indent-tabs-mode` to `nil`.\n",
